FT  21 APR 93 / Bank Negara chief defends forex loss
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KIERAN COOKE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   KUALA LUMPUR
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
BANK NEGARA, Malaysia's central bank, has defended itself against criticism
that it has gambled on foreign exchange markets with resulting massive
losses in its special reserves, writes Kieran Cooke in Kuala Lumpur.
In its annual report for last year, the bank said it had suffered a MDollars
2.7bn (Pounds 686m) contingent liability on forward foreign exchange
