<TEXT>
Gunmen have killed families, gang-raped women and forced civilians from
their homes under threat of death during savage Moslem-Croat fighting in
central Bosnia, UN sources told Reuter in Sarajevo yesterday. They said UN
relief workers had found bodies of execution victims - unidentified gunmen
were reported to have shot entire families in the head at point blank range
 -and seen homes looted in the Vitez, Zenica and Travnik areas, where
battles erupted last week between the nominal allies in Bosnia's civil war.
Heavy fighting continued yesterday, but Bosnian radio reported the two sides
had agreed to order a ceasefire.
