FT  20 APR 93 / UK Company News: Five Oaks hit by Pounds 1m provision
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
AFTER providing a further Pounds 1m against write-downs in investment and
development properties, Five Oaks Investment saw its pre-tax losses increase
from Pounds 371,000 to Pounds 953,000 in the six months ended December 31
1992.
Although the company felt the property market was bottoming out it was
thought prudent to provide for a further write-down, explained Mr Trevor
Robinson, chairman.
On a brighter note, he said rental income now exceeded all interest and
other outgoings; in the half year the surplus, with other income, was Pounds
50,000 against a deficit of Pounds 578,000.
Apart from rising rents and diminishing voids, the improved performance
reflected lower borrowings following the sale of the Hanley property and
strict control of overheads.
Losses per share came to 2.04p (0.8p).
