permission to take a larger stake in Australia's John Fairfax newspaper
group.
Mr Dawkins has until the end of the week to decide whether to allow Mr
Black's UK-based Telegraph group to raise its holding in Fairfax from 15 to
25 per cent.
The federal cabinet is likely to discuss the application today.
The application has attracted criticism from a wide range of public figures,
including Mr Martin Ferguson, president of the Australian Council of Trade
Unions (ACTU), and Mr Malcolm Fraser, a former conservative prime minister.
